What you need to know:

A member of Union Omaha staff said if Otieno was called in to the national team, the entire organization would celebrate his achievement. For now, Otieno focuses on what he can control: improving his game, developing as a player, and doing whatever he can to help his team win.Otieno’s move to Omaha is a giant step in his career. A step that is mutually beneficial to both himself and his club. It certainly appears Otieno’s best is yet to come.  